rComments: Dr. Krein is a very intelligent and helpful teacher. He is a great researcher and is one of the most helpful professors outside of class if you don't understand something.
Overall good teacher. You have to put in work for the class but you get a lot out of it (if you're interested). Sometimes he uses MathCAD which is hard to follow.
I recommend reading before coming to lecture... it is hard to follow at times. He is not very organized, but he is very informative and helpful.
Good teacher. A little hard to understand at times, but very helpful in office hours. One of the very few people I have come across that are good researchers as well as great teachers.
